Title: Simple Pancake Recipe
Author: Jane Doe
Servings: 4
Time: 10 minutes prep, 15 minutes cook

Tools:
- Mixing bowl
- Whisk
- Non-stick skillet
- Measuring cups
- Measuring spoons

Ingredients:
Dry Ingredients:
- 2 cups flour [Note: Use all-purpose flour] [Image: https://example.com/flour.jpg]
- 2 tablespoons sugar
- 2 teaspoons baking powder [Note: Can substitute with baking soda]
- 1/2 teaspoon salt

Wet Ingredients:
- 2 eggs
- 1 1/2 cups milk
- 2 tablespoons melted butter [Note: Allow to cool before adding] [Image: https://example.com/butter.jpg]

Instructions:
Step 1: Prepare the Batter
1. Whisk together the flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt in a large bowl. [Note: Sift for a lighter batter] [Image: https://example.com/batter.jpg]
2. In another bowl, beat the eggs and add milk and melted butter. [Note: Use room temperature ingredients]
3. Pour the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients and stir until just combined.

Step 2: Cook the Pancakes
4. Heat a non-stick skillet over medium heat. [Note: Test with a drop of water] [Image: https://example.com/skillet.jpg]
5. Pour 1/4 cup batter for each pancake.
6. Cook until bubbles form on the surface, then flip and cook until golden brown.
7. Serve with syrup, butter, or your choice of toppings.

Notes:
- You can substitute whole milk with a dairy-free alternative.
- Add chocolate chips or blueberries to the batter for variety.